	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> " He was the founder of cenobitic monasticism. He was born of pagan parents\n                  in Upper Egypt. His first contact with\n                  Christianity occurred in 312, when he was a conscript in the Roman\n                  army. Then, Pachomius came into contact\n                  with several well known ascetics and decided to pursue that path under the\n                  guidance of the hermit named Palamon.\n                  Finally, he established his own monastery in between 318 and 323. " .
